ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 3. What is your attitude toward talking with a therapist/counselor as treatment for your problem? (Select one)
Notes: 1= Very positive; 2= Moderately positive; 3= A little positive; 4= Neutral; 5= A little negative; 6= Moderately negative; 7= Very negative

ElementDescription: 4. What is your attitude toward taking medication as treatment for your problem? (Select one)
Notes: 1= Very positive; 2= Moderately positive; 3= A little positive; 4= Neutral; 5= A little negative; 6= Moderately negative; 7= Very negative

ElementDescription: 5. Overall, how much improvement do you expect to experience as a result of treatment? (Select one)
Notes: -3= I expect to feel much worse; -2= -2; -1= -1; 0= No change; 1= +1; 2= +2; 3= I expect to feel much better

ElementDescription: How suitable do you think this treatment is for your problem?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 5= Moderate; 10= Extremely Suitable

ElementDescription: How successful do you think your treatment here will be?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 5= Moderate; 10= Extremely Suitable
